        "description": "This test case takes a filename. It determines the size of the file, and attempts to check whether the size of the file is smaller than 128 characters. The arithmetic used in the if-check may cause an integer underflow, which will result in the if-check succeeding when it should fail. If the if-check succeeds after an integer underflow, a large amount of data is copied into a small (128-character) buffer on the stack. This will overwrite memory on the stack, resulting in segmentation fault upon return from the function.\nMetadata\n - Base program: Subversion\n - Source Taint: FILE_CONTENTS\n - Data Type: TYPEDEF\n - Data Flow: ADDRESS_AS_LINEAR_EXPRESSION\n - Control Flow: SET_JUMP_LONG_JUMP",
